You can get the last GuaraScript version at
http://www.guarascript.org

LINUX (UNIX) SYSTEMS

To install the GuaraScript interpreter on a Linux machine:

1) Unpack the distribution file:
    tar xvzf guash-x.y.z.tar.gz
2) Enter the distribution directory:
    cd guash-x.y.z/
3) Clean up the distribution directory:
    make clean
4) Copile the source code:
    make
    make ./bin/glutguash
    make ./bin/glwmguash
5) Install binaries:
    make install
    make install_glutguash
    make install_glwmguash
6) Install syntax highlight for GTK based IDEs:
    make install_language_specs

glguash is the GuaraScript interpreter with the OpenGL, GLU, GLUT and GLUTIL extensions
built in. glguash is neccessary in order to run the OpenGL examples provided with guash.

WINDOWS

To install the GuaraScript interpreter on a Windows machine:

1) Unpack the distribution file;
2) Double-click on an example program, on the examples/opengl folder.
   When prompted to inform the application to run the script,
   select glguash.exe, in the bin directory of the distribution.

MAC OS X

To install the GuaraScript interpreter on a Mac OS X machine:

1) Create the target directory:
    mkdir /usr/local
    mkdir /usr/local/bin
2) Unpack the distribution file:
    tar xvzf guash-x.y.z.zip
3) Enter the distribution directory:
    cd guash-x.y.z/
4) Clean up the distribution directory:
    make clean
5) Copile the source code:
    make -f Makefile.MacOSX
    make -f Makefile.MacOSX ./bin/glutguash
    make -f Makefile.MacOSX ./bin/glwmguash
6) Install binaries:
    make -f Makefile.MacOSX install
    make -f Makefile.MacOSX install_glutguash
    make -f Makefile.MacOSX install_glwmguash
6) Install syntax highlight for GTK based IDEs:
    make install_language_specs

